1) How to install and Administer Oracle Rest Data Services
https://www.oracle.com/webfolder/technetwork/tutorials/obe/db/ords/r30/Install_Administer_ORDS/Install_Administer_ORDS.html#section4
( You might face firewall issues )
If you face error like sql dev / ords / params. properties ( access is denied ).. 
that means you are not able to write in that location and you need to install Oracle SQL Developer in another location. After that try installation process again. 
( https://community.oracle.com/tech/developers/discussion/4127184/sqldev-ords-params-properties-permission-denied-when-trying-to-install-ords-using-sql-developer)
To access UTL_HTTP Package, user needs to get access. 
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26369834/stored-procedure-error-pls-00201-identifier-utl-http-must-be-declared
You might face memory issues if you configure ORDS in your system. 
https://community.oracle.com/tech/apps-infra/discussion/4035353/there-is-insufficient-memory-for-the-java-runtime-environment-to-continue-error-in-weblogic-12c-ser
For ACL issues, try the below
https://virtual-dba.com/blog/resolving-the-ora-24247/#:~:text=The%20best%20solution%20to%20the,ACL%20for%20the%20given%20host.

